	   <tr><td colspan=2>As a monkey if you are fighting with your fists STA is never a problem, as I recall.&nbsp;&nbsp;It's only once you pick up weapons that STA will take a hit.<br><br>I'm trying to remember if I got tired when fighting as a young monkey using only my meat clubs, but I don't recall that I did.<br><br>Either that or it's the jum-jum juice that is affecting my memory...<br><br>See the post I made below for my relief for fatigue-- that and ask for several "Spirit Pouches" from that friendly shammy.  It always amazes me how few monks will ask me to make these for them even when grouped together.  I suppose it's a form of institutional memory when way back  pre-Kunark if you died your conjured items disappeared off your body.  However, all that has changed with subsequent patches, so unless you have a bad connection and you get kicked offline, there is no danger of losing all your newly looted wealth from the freshly opened can of "Whoopass" (tm) being wielded by that Sandgiant the inconsiderate boob in the group next to yours just trained on you.<br><br>People spend inordinate amounts of cash to buy weight reducing packs and bags when they are free just for the asking from that hungry troll shaman nearby who keeps creeping you out by drooling whenever he looks your way (don't worry about him, he is just thinking of different ways to cook you.  He's harmless-- unless you're on a PvP server.  then you are in SERIOUS trouble!).  And they are 100% weight reducing to boot.<br><br>Oh.  Mages or wizzies (I'm not sure which) make them too, but who wants to deal with those arrogant bastards who refuse to get their hands dirty from fighting?<br><br>Good luck, young monkeys!<br><br>--Pusbag, Uber-shaman, friend and diety to lucky monks everywhere<br>--proud owner of a monkey in the 47th Baboon Troop<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
