	   <tr><td colspan=2> Ooh yeah, the magicians will try and get you with their bags. They leave them lying around newbie areas and don't tell you that they disappear when you log out. Then you *that'd be me when I was a new dummie* pick it up, put all your valuable heavy items into it, and log out. When you log in again, everything is *poof!*. I had to learn the hard way. Now I think the bags actually say No Rent, thank goodness. <br> Point? Point? Oh yeah, there's a point somewhere. I just wanted to corroborate what Pus said about asking a shaman for a spirit pouch. I played a shaman for a bit and never ever used this spell. I guess I was so big and strong that I never was overweight, so when people asked me to conjure one up for 'em, I was more than happy to do so. Just put your items inside and they magically lose weight ;) <br> Another thing you can use if you are trying to keep your weight down, is to buy a kit for one of the tradeskills. I use a tailoring kit myself. Actually I use two or three of them. I don't remember the exact weight but I think they're each less than .5, which even us monkies can understand is much less than the 3 pound backpacks that many of you still might be carrying around. Just be sure not to hit that 'combine' button ;)<br>&nbsp;<br>Beleni<br>Lowly Monk on Karana</td></tr>
