	   <tr><td colspan=2> I don't know that I believe what was said above. I don't think that going over the 14 weight limit will make you lose stamina quicker, make you not hit as hard, and take more damage when you get hit.<br> It's not that the poster is wrong, I just don't think that has been true in my case and I think it would be worth testing out further. <br> I often, very very often go over the fourteen pound weight limit. Sometimes only by a few pounds, sometimes by a lot, but I have never noticed myself getting hit more often, hitting with less power, etc. <br> I think that the original poster is merely describing what happens when he gets very low on HP which is a very common occurrence. First of all, the poster is level 7, and says that in fights that last over a minute this is happening. I think that if you were to time an average fight at level 7, the minute mark is where you'd start getting pretty low on health if you were fighting an even conning opponent. And then we all understand the feeling that's being described. That's what I call the 'too late to run' feeling, where you turn around and try to run, only to be moving at one quarter your speed, while the mob is giving you a swift boot to the back-side with every step ;)<br> Anyway, to the original poster, I would suggest that you watch that 14 pound weight limit carefully anyway. Whether it affects stamina or not, it really does do a number big time on your armor class. I tested it out one day after reading that somewhere and realized that only being three or four pounds over the limit can REALLY mean a big drop in AC. Everybody is right, it's not worth the drop just to be carrying around a few extra coppers. Don't get addicted to large amounts of money. You have been warned!!! <br>&nbsp;<br>Beleni<br>Lowly Monk on Karana</td></tr>
